
This program searches for files and directories to rename
Files have to match starting with the "find" argument and the matching 
text is replaced with the "replace" arg.
The program starts in the directory provided with the "start"
and searches exatly "level" arg levels downward

Usage ./renameFiles.sh find replace start levels
find: the string to sarch for
replace: the string to replace it with
start: the starting directory
levels: the number of subdirectories to search